# System Blueprint

Map the full system architecture across all configured surfaces.

## Surfaces
- List frontend panels, backend services, shared libraries, and integration boundaries.
- `Huz-Web-Frontend` protected support surface now centers on `src/routes/AppRoutes.jsx`, `src/pages/UserSetting/Support/help.jsx`, `src/pages/UserSetting/OperatorResponse/operatorresponse.jsx`, `src/pages/UserSetting/sidebar.jsx`, and the profile menu in `src/components/Header/Header.js`.
- `Huz-Backend` keeps support ownership split between `booking/views/api_v1.py` for booking-scoped mutations and `booking/views/support.py` for current-user complaint/request history lists.

## Runtime Topology
- Describe entrypoints, deployment/runtime boundaries, and cross-surface interactions.
- Authenticated traveler support flow is now: protected web route (`/help` or `/operator-response`) -> `supportApi.js` / `bookingApi.js` -> shared `httpClient` auth transport -> Django `/api/v1` support endpoints.
- `/messages` remains outside the live support topology in this run; it is still a mock-only UI and does not consume the backend `chat` surface.
- Backend verification topology now has a local-only path for automated checks: `manage.py` -> `huz.settings_test` -> SQLite test database, leaving production `.env` MySQL wiring untouched.
